{"article_id":"MyuGNHYewnyjEnJ3","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"ORLANDO , Fla. -","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"Florida has reported 37,439 positive coronavirus cases and 1,471 deaths ,","depth":4},{"id":2,"text":"ranking it eighth in the U.S. for the number of confirmed cases","depth":5},{"id":3,"text":"despite being the nation ' s third most populated state .","depth":5},{"id":4,"text":"The case and death numbers point to something","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"many may find surprising :","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"Florida has not become as much of a hot spot as other states such as New York , California and Michigan .","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"The state has fewer cases per capita than other heavily impacted states , such as Louisiana .","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"According to Johns Hopkins University ,","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"Florida has had a total of 176 cases per 100,000 people","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"compared to Louisiana ,","depth":10},{"id":11,"text":"which has had 644 per 100,000 people .","depth":10},{"id":12,"text":"Most of the Sunshine State entered its first phase","depth":6},{"id":13,"text":"of reopening on Monday ,","depth":6},{"id":14,"text":"with restaurants , retail stores and museums allowed to operate at no more 25 percent capacity with social distancing restrictions .","depth":5},{"id":15,"text":"Gov . Ron DeSantis","depth":5},{"id":16,"text":"Ronald Dion DeSantisThe Hill 's Campaign Report :","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"Biden 's virtual campaign swings through Florida 's Morning Report","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"- Presented by Facebook -","depth":6},{"id":19,"text":"In reversal , Trump says","depth":5},{"id":20,"text":"he wo n't disband coronavirus task force","depth":5},{"id":21,"text":"Florida emerges as bright spot in COVID-19 fight","depth":4},{"id":22,"text":"MORE ( R ) ,","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"who took criticism last month for his initial reluctance","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"to issue a statewide stay-at-home order ,","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"touted the progress","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"his state has made","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"in a press conference on Tuesday .","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"\" The fact of the matter is , Florida has met all the gating criteria","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"to be into phase one , \"","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"DeSantis said at a press briefing on Tuesday .","depth":8},{"id":31,"text":"Experts say","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"there are a variety of reasons ,","depth":11},{"id":33,"text":"including individual willingness","depth":12},{"id":34,"text":"to self-quarantine ,","depth":12},{"id":35,"text":"that could explain","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"why the state appears to have avoided being hit harder by the virus .","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"The state ' s most populated counties in South Florida , as well as Orange County , home to the greater Orlando area , were under stay-at-home orders prior to the governor ' s statewide order","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"issued on April 1 .","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"Early actions from local governments could have contributed to stopping the spread of the virus in the state ,","depth":11},{"id":40,"text":"according to government and health officials .","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"\" We put a safer-at-home order quickly ,","depth":13},{"id":42,"text":"and then tried our best to over-communicate that","depth":14},{"id":43,"text":"so that everyone understood the significance of it , \"","depth":14},{"id":44,"text":"Tampa Mayor Jane Castor","depth":14},{"id":45,"text":"( D )","depth":14},{"id":46,"text":"told .","depth":13},{"id":47,"text":"\" Our community understood the level of personal responsibility","depth":12},{"id":48,"text":"and took it very seriously . \"","depth":12},{"id":49,"text":"Miami-Dade County Mayor Carlos Gimenez","depth":11},{"id":50,"text":"( R )","depth":11},{"id":51,"text":"said","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"DeSantis ' s initial focus on South Florida played an early role","depth":11},{"id":53,"text":"in combating the spread .","depth":11},{"id":54,"text":"\" He very wisely understood","depth":14},{"id":55,"text":"that the situation in southeast Florida was different than the rest of the state , \"","depth":14},{"id":56,"text":"Gimenez said .","depth":13},{"id":57,"text":"\" He ' s been right on .","depth":12},{"id":58,"text":"He ' s known","depth":12},{"id":59,"text":"that it ' s a big , big state","depth":13},{"id":60,"text":"and that the orders can not be uniform throughout the state . \"","depth":13},{"id":61,"text":"Florida has a large elderly population ,","depth":11},{"id":62,"text":"which raised fears","depth":12},{"id":63,"text":"it could suffer from a high number of COVID-19 fatalities .","depth":12},{"id":64,"text":"Images of young people","depth":12},{"id":65,"text":"partying over spring break in the state","depth":12},{"id":66,"text":"compounded some fears .","depth":11},{"id":67,"text":"But experts say","depth":12},{"id":68,"text":"many in the state appeared to take a diligent approach on their own to COVID-19 .","depth":12},{"id":69,"text":"\" Many older people self-quarantined","depth":14},{"id":70,"text":"before being told to do so by the governor , \"","depth":14},{"id":71,"text":"said Laurence Barton , a crisis management and public safety professor at the University of Central Florida .","depth":13},{"id":72,"text":"\" That decision by an older population may have well saved , in my opinion , tens of thousands of lives . \"","depth":12},{"id":73,"text":"Cindy Prins , a health care epidemiology professor at the University of Florida , said","depth":12},{"id":74,"text":"that coverage of Florida ' s crowded beaches over spring break in March also likely drove a number of the state ' s residents to self-quarantine in an effort","depth":13},{"id":75,"text":"to protect themselves .","depth":13},{"id":76,"text":"\" People got some information","depth":14},{"id":77,"text":"about what we should be doing","depth":14},{"id":78,"text":"as opposed to what we were seeing , \"","depth":13},{"id":79,"text":"Prins said .","depth":12},{"id":80,"text":"Other experts say","depth":11},{"id":81,"text":"they are perplexed by the coronavirus ' s impact on Florida so far ,","depth":12},{"id":82,"text":"citing luck as a potential factor .","depth":12},{"id":83,"text":"\" Other aspects are just luck .","depth":10},{"id":84,"text":"It hasn ' t gotten to some places yet ,","depth":11},{"id":85,"text":"but it may still be on its way , \"","depth":11},{"id":86,"text":"said Roger Shapiro , associate professor of immunology and infectious diseases at Harvard University ' s T.H . Chan School of Public Health .","depth":10},{"id":87,"text":"He warned","depth":9},{"id":88,"text":"that Floridians should not get a false sense of security .","depth":9},{"id":89,"text":"\" The virus is still on the move ,","depth":10},{"id":90,"text":"and it can still travel to new places in the world ,","depth":11},{"id":91,"text":"and it may still be finding inroads into some of the states and some of the countries","depth":12},{"id":92,"text":"that are so far less affected , \"","depth":12},{"id":93,"text":"he said .","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"Government officials and public health experts in the state have continued to urge caution ,","depth":10},{"id":95,"text":"citing the possibility of a second wave in the latter half of the year .","depth":10},{"id":96,"text":"\" I don ' t think","depth":12},{"id":97,"text":"you need to totally take your foot off the pedal , \"","depth":12},{"id":98,"text":"said Panama City Mayor Greg Brudnicki said .","depth":11},{"id":99,"text":"\" People don ' t need to get this false sense of security","depth":11},{"id":100,"text":"that we don ' t need to do the social distancing","depth":12},{"id":101,"text":"and do the things","depth":13},{"id":102,"text":"we need to do . \"","depth":13},{"id":103,"text":"Bay County ,","depth":10},{"id":104,"text":"which includes Panama City ,","depth":10},{"id":105,"text":"has only seen 76 positive coronavirus cases .","depth":9},{"id":106,"text":"Experts also point to the importance of testing ,","depth":11},{"id":107,"text":"which Florida officials say","depth":12},{"id":108,"text":"they are looking to improve across the state .","depth":12},{"id":109,"text":"Johns Hopkins University ranked Florida 22nd in per capita testing ,","depth":11},{"id":110,"text":"performing a total of 2,186 tests per 100,000 people as of Tuesday .","depth":11},{"id":111,"text":"DeSantis announced new plans","depth":12},{"id":112,"text":"to expand testing in the state on Wednesday ,","depth":12},{"id":113,"text":"permitting tests to be performed at pharmacies as well as the random checking of blood donations for antibodies","depth":12},{"id":114,"text":"that show","depth":13},{"id":115,"text":"whether someone has recovered from the virus .","depth":13},{"id":116,"text":"The governor also introduced on Wednesday the state ' s first mobile testing facility ,","depth":12},{"id":117,"text":"through which 500 rapid tests ,","depth":14},{"id":118,"text":"each lasting 45 minutes ,","depth":14},{"id":119,"text":"would be processed a day .","depth":13},{"id":120,"text":"The tests are currently available at the Hard Rock Stadium site in Miami Gardens","depth":12},{"id":121,"text":"and will soon be available in Orlando and Jacksonville .","depth":12},{"id":122,"text":"\" Obviously the hospitals need it ,","depth":11},{"id":123,"text":"but then the next things are the nursing homes and the long-term care facilities","depth":11},{"id":124,"text":"because it can really be a game-changer","depth":11},{"id":125,"text":"and","depth":12},{"id":126,"text":"if applied properly","depth":13},{"id":127,"text":"can save lives , \"","depth":13},{"id":128,"text":"DeSantis said .","depth":9}],"relations":[{"parent":257,"left":0,"right":256,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":256,"left":142,"right":255,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":142